    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX II BRAKE MONITOR SYSTEM - DESCRIPTION - FLOW SWITCH</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>FLOW SWITCH</title>
        <para>The flow switch provides input to the Hydro-Max monitor and thus turns on the warning light, alarm, and
            booster pump when there is not sufficient flow of power steering fluid to the Hydro-Max brake booster unit.
            This switch contains normally closed contacts.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
